# AI Trust Assessment Rubric

## Assessment Overview
**Total Points:** 100  
**Assessment Type:** Formative and Summative  
**Evaluation Method:** Multi-criteria assessment using four key criteria

## Assessment Criteria

### 1. Understanding of Trust Pillars (25 points)
**Weight:** 25% of total grade

| Score Range | Description | Specific Requirements |
|-------------|-------------|----------------------|
| **Excellent (23-25 points)** | Demonstrates comprehensive understanding of all six trust pillars with specific examples | • Accurately defines all six pillars<br>• Provides 2+ relevant examples for each pillar<br>• Explains interconnections between pillars<br>• Shows deep understanding of healthcare applications |
| **Good (18-22 points)** | Shows good understanding of most trust pillars with some examples | • Defines 4-5 pillars accurately<br>• Provides 1-2 examples for most pillars<br>• Shows basic understanding of relationships<br>• Demonstrates adequate healthcare knowledge |
| **Satisfactory (13-17 points)** | Shows basic understanding of trust pillars with limited examples | • Defines 3-4 pillars correctly<br>• Provides 1 example for some pillars<br>• Limited explanation of relationships<br>• Basic healthcare understanding |
| **Needs Improvement (0-12 points)** | Limited understanding of trust pillars with few or no examples | • Defines fewer than 3 pillars<br>• Provides minimal or no examples<br>• No understanding of relationships<br>• Lacks healthcare context |

### 2. Healthcare AI Analysis (30 points)
**Weight:** 30% of total grade

| Score Range | Description | Specific Requirements |
|-------------|-------------|----------------------|
| **Excellent (27-30 points)** | Provides insightful analysis of healthcare AI systems with multiple perspectives | • Analyzes 3+ healthcare AI systems<br>• Considers technical, ethical, and social perspectives<br>• Identifies specific trust challenges<br>• Proposes well-reasoned solutions |
| **Good (21-26 points)** | Provides good analysis with some consideration of different perspectives | • Analyzes 2-3 healthcare AI systems<br>• Considers 2 perspectives adequately<br>• Identifies some trust challenges<br>• Proposes reasonable solutions |
| **Satisfactory (15-20 points)** | Provides basic analysis with limited consideration of perspectives | • Analyzes 1-2 healthcare AI systems<br>• Limited perspective consideration<br>• Identifies basic trust challenges<br>• Proposes simple solutions |
| **Needs Improvement (0-14 points)** | Analysis is superficial or missing key elements | • Analyzes fewer than 2 systems<br>• Single perspective only<br>• Misses key trust challenges<br>• Solutions are inadequate or missing |

### 3. Trust Scoring Application (25 points)
**Weight:** 25% of total grade

| Score Range | Description | Specific Requirements |
|-------------|-------------|----------------------|
| **Excellent (23-25 points)** | Accurately applies trust scoring methodology with clear justification | • Uses SYMBI platform correctly<br>• Provides detailed justification for scores<br>• Considers all relevant factors<br>• Scores are consistent and logical |
| **Good (18-22 points)** | Generally accurate application with some justification | • Uses platform with minor errors<br>• Provides some justification<br>• Considers most relevant factors<br>• Scores are mostly consistent |
| **Satisfactory (13-17 points)** | Basic application with limited justification | • Uses platform with several errors<br>• Limited justification provided<br>• Considers some relevant factors<br>• Scores show some inconsistency |
| **Needs Improvement (0-12 points)** | Inaccurate application or missing justification | • Major errors in platform use<br>• Little or no justification<br>• Ignores relevant factors<br>• Scores are inconsistent or illogical |

### 4. Ethical Considerations (20 points)
**Weight:** 20% of total grade

| Score Range | Description | Specific Requirements |
|-------------|-------------|----------------------|
| **Excellent (18-20 points)** | Thoughtfully considers ethical implications with well-reasoned arguments | • Identifies 3+ ethical issues<br>• Provides well-reasoned arguments<br>• Considers stakeholder perspectives<br>• Proposes ethical solutions |
| **Good (14-17 points)** | Considers ethical implications with some reasoning | • Identifies 2-3 ethical issues<br>• Provides adequate reasoning<br>• Considers some stakeholder perspectives<br>• Proposes reasonable solutions |
| **Satisfactory (10-13 points)** | Basic consideration of ethical implications | • Identifies 1-2 ethical issues<br>• Limited reasoning provided<br>• Basic stakeholder consideration<br>• Simple solutions proposed |
| **Needs Improvement (0-9 points)** | Limited or no consideration of ethical implications | • Identifies fewer than 2 issues<br>• Little or no reasoning<br>• Ignores stakeholder perspectives<br>• Inadequate or missing solutions |

## Assessment Methods

### Formative Assessment (40 points)
- **Class Participation:** 15 points
- **Trust Scoring Exercise:** 15 points
- **Group Discussion Contribution:** 10 points

### Summative Assessment (60 points)
- **End-of-Session Quiz:** 20 points
- **Homework Assignment:** 25 points
- **Case Study Analysis:** 15 points

## Grading Scale
- **A (90-100 points):** Excellent understanding and application
- **B (80-89 points):** Good understanding and application
- **C (70-79 points):** Satisfactory understanding and application
- **D (60-69 points):** Basic understanding, needs improvement
- **F (0-59 points):** Inadequate understanding and application

## Feedback Guidelines

### For Excellent Performance
- Acknowledge exceptional insight and analysis
- Suggest opportunities for deeper exploration
- Encourage peer mentoring opportunities

### For Good Performance
- Affirm strong understanding
- Suggest specific areas for improvement
- Provide additional challenging examples

### For Satisfactory Performance
- Identify specific knowledge gaps
- Provide targeted resources for improvement
- Suggest additional practice opportunities

### For Needs Improvement
- Clearly identify areas needing significant improvement
- Provide specific remediation strategies
- Offer additional support and resources
- Schedule follow-up assessment

## Submission Requirements

### Format Requirements
- Typed, double-spaced, 12-point font
- Include name, date, and case study ID
- Proper citations for external sources
- Clear organization with headings

### Content Requirements
- Address all four assessment criteria
- Provide specific examples and evidence
- Use proper technical terminology
- Demonstrate critical thinking

### Deadline
- Submit by end of class session for in-class work
- Homework due at next class session
- Late submissions penalized 10% per day

## Academic Integrity
- All work must be original
- Proper citation required for external sources
- Collaboration allowed only as specified
- Plagiarism will result in assignment failure

